  (text "Compact Gotek core  -  circuit derived from CDO's Issue 1.1 design (theoddys.com)\nGotek-compatible floppy emulator for the BBC Master internal 34-way floppy header.\nProgramming: fit BOOT0 link LK1, connect 3V3 FTDI to PL2, use STM32CubeProgrammer; firmware: FlashFloppy.\nNOTE: Do not use with an external floppy drive connected at the same time (no open-collector drivers)."
    (at 25.4 280.67 0) (effects (font (size 2 2)) (justify left bottom)) (uuid a40faa24-459e-482a-92a8-bb652cf2ba8b))
  (text "Buffers 3V3 MCU outputs to 5V TTL:\nIndex, Track0, Write Protect, Read Data"
    (at 240.03 41.91 0) (effects (font (size 1.5 1.5)) (justify left bottom)) (uuid cd2cc8b9-d872-457b-9d54-13a28914fe85))
  (text "1K pull-ups (R6-R11) on host-driven inputs"
    (at 300.99 198.12 0) (effects (font (size 1.5 1.5)) (justify left bottom)) (uuid ba66fe60-57d0-4ae5-b3f7-83715eaf9902))
  (text "SK1: 34-pin boxed IDC header (top side),\nstandard floppy ribbon pinout"
    (at 340.36 170.18 0) (effects (font (size 1.5 1.5)) (justify left bottom)) (uuid e4fdd85b-5a3e-49b9-8c4f-66e8b2b812e5))
  (text "PL1 -> 5V power in   PL2 -> FTDI (3V3) programming   PL3 -> USB-A breakout (stick)\nPL4 -> sound out   PL5 -> 0.96in OLED (I2C)   PL6 -> KY-040 style rotary encoder\nSK1 -> 34-pin boxed IDC, standard Shugart floppy bus"
    (at 25.4 236.22 0) (effects (font (size 1.5 1.5)) (justify left bottom)) (uuid 2f142969-0766-4f6e-9353-24fabc064d3b))

